    <a title="Colette Lamberth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/35556770-colette-lamberth"><img alt="Colette Lamberth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1472311736p2/35556770.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1671469163?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Colette Lamberth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Colette Lamberth" href="/user/show/35556770-colette-lamberth">Colette Lamberth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/13413248-forever-is-over">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1671469163" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16090303596179087770">I really enjoyed this book but I think I might have loved it if it had been a third shorter. It was nice to take a trip down memory lane and I could relate to all the 70s and 80s storylines but ultimately it just took too long to reach the conclusion, particularly knowing from the first chapter where we were headed. The details say it was re-formatted in June 2015 but it is riddled with typos and formatting issues which were the reason I didn&apos;t finish it at my first attempt to read it. I read it</span>
  <span id="freeText16090303596179087770" style="display:none">I really enjoyed this book but I think I might have loved it if it had been a third shorter. It was nice to take a trip down memory lane and I could relate to all the 70s and 80s storylines but ultimately it just took too long to reach the conclusion, particularly knowing from the first chapter where we were headed. The details say it was re-formatted in June 2015 but it is riddled with typos and formatting issues which were the reason I didn't finish it at my first attempt to read it. I read it this time after a strong recommendation from a friend and I'm glad I did. I liked the author's style so I may read his other books.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16090303596179087770" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

